<Layout title="Understanding Car Rental Insurance | Tomobil Car Hire">
  <main class="min-h-screen py-16">
    <article class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-3xl">
      <header class="mb-8">
        <div class="text-gray-500 mb-2">April 5, 2025</div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Understanding Car Rental Insurance Options</h1>
      </header>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>
          Car rental insurance can be complex and confusing. This comprehensive guide will help you 
          understand the different types of coverage available and make an informed decision about 
          what protection you need.
        </p>

        <h2>Types of Rental Car Insurance</h2>
        
        <h3>1. Collision Damage Waiver (CDW)</h3>
        <p>
          Also known as Loss Damage Waiver (LDW), this isn't technically insurance but rather a waiver 
          that releases you from financial responsibility if the rental car is damaged or stolen.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Covers damage to the rental vehicle</li>
          <li>May have deductibles</li>
          <li>Usually the most expensive option</li>
          <li>Might be redundant if covered by your credit card</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2. Liability Insurance</h3>
        <p>
          This covers damage you might cause to other people's property or injuries to other people 
          while driving the rental car.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Required by law in most places</li>
          <li>May be included in the basic rental rate</li>
          <li>Consider supplemental liability if basic coverage is low</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3. Personal Accident Insurance</h3>
        <p>
          Covers medical costs for you and your passengers in case of an accident.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>May be redundant if you have health insurance</li>
          <li>Usually includes ambulance and death benefits</li>
          <li>Consider if traveling internationally</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4. Personal Effects Coverage</h3>
        <p>
          Protects your personal belongings in the rental car from theft or damage.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>May be covered by your homeowner's or renter's insurance</li>
          <li>Consider for high-value items</li>
          <li>Check coverage limits</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Existing Coverage You May Have</h2>
        <p>
          Before purchasing rental car insurance, check these sources of coverage:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Personal auto insurance policy</li>
          <li>Credit card benefits</li>
          <li>Travel insurance</li>
          <li>Health insurance (for medical coverage)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Making the Right Choice</h2>
        <p>
          To determine what coverage you need:
        </p>
        <ol>
          <li>Check your existing coverage</li>
          <li>Understand the rental company's requirements</li>
          <li>Consider your destination and trip type</li>
          <li>Evaluate your risk tolerance</li>
        </ol>

        <p>
          Remember, while rental car insurance might seem expensive, it can provide valuable peace 
          of mind and financial protection. Always read the terms and conditions carefully before 
          making your decision.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
